<TITLE> Pietersen leaving World T20 for birth of first child </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BRIDGETOWN, Barbados, May 9 (bdnews24.com/AFP) -- England batsman Kevin Pietersen is to return home from the World Twenty20 in the Caribbean to be with his pregnant wife for the birth of the couple's first child. Following his match-winning innings of 53 against his native South Africa in a 39-run victory at the Kensington Oval here on Saturday, Pietersen said he would be flying to London within the next 24 hours. However, he expects to return to the West Indies should England qualify for the semi-finals, barring complications. "It's my first child so it's a hell of an exciting time for me," Pietersen told Sky Sports 2. "I'll be dashing across the Atlantic and hopefully dashing back," added Pietersen, who before the tournament had come to an agreement with the England and Wales Cricket Board (ECB) allowing him to dash back at a moment's notice to be with his pop star wife Jessica. "I'm flying back to London in the next 24 hours and hoping everything goes well and according to plan, there's no complications," Pietersen said. "If we get through to the semi-finals, I'll come in the day before the semi-fin
